column5: Does anyone know of a private cabin to go fishing on the rainy lake?Two families want to share a place, and we will have our boats with us. Not interested in the resort type places.......

Two options off the top of my head.1. [email protected] guys name is Dave he has a low cost island based place for rent.2. http://www.elksbay.com/ Nice low cost whole mainland house for rent.If you need more let me know......dw
I have a 3 bedroom cottage that I rent out by the week-its on an island but close to mainland and marinas [email protected] for pics and info-thanks Walli

I am not sure but I think if you planning on doing a private rental on the Canadian side it might be on the virge of being illegal. Might want to check with the MNR so you don't get yourself in a bind.
hi fitch, got a cottage to rent on rainy. it is legal and have been doing it for some time. it is not for everybody as you are on your own.there are no services like you find at lodges.
hi have you a cabin for rent in late oct. is drive to and how much / monthly [email protected]
